Rating: 0
I have made this dish often. I use fresh spinach pasta to complement the color of the sauce and use fresh basil instead of oregano. I would suggest using less olive oil and caramelizing the egg plant instead of frying it. Brown first and then slowly cook the eggplant in it's own sugars until it is cooked. Less greasy and the juices of the eggplant are not lost by taking it out of the pan. The addition of black pitless olives at the last stage makes this dish even better.

